-- Kuwait Deploys Guards on Oil Tankers to Fight Piracy, KUNA Says
-- B y   N a y l a   R a z z o u k
-- 2012-10-01T12:37:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-01/kuwait-deploys-guards-on-oil-tankers-to-fight-piracy-kuna-says.html
Kuwait Oil Tanker Co. started to use
armed guards aboard its oil and natural gas tankers to protect
against pirates, the state-run Kuwait News Agency reported,
citing Chairman and Managing Director Bader Alkhashti.  KOTC agreed with security-service providers to deploy
guards trained to handle dangerous situations, Alkhashti said,
according to the report today. The company has 24 tankers of
various capacities and will start building six more ships in
2014, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nayla Razzouk in Dubai at 
